# -------------------------- GENERAL --------------------------

# *****
# The meaning of the variables below should be obvious (i.e.; "num_alchemist"
# is used to stored the number of alchemists in the town/city/village). The
# use of "SF" is a means to determine how many services or businesses of a
# given type exist in the town. It is used by the group "GenNumMacro".
#
# The "SF" value is the number of people that are needed to support one
# business/service of the type given. Using the defaults as examples, this
# means that for every 3000 people in a town, you will find an armorer; for
# every 700 people, you'll find a cooper, and so forth. The group "GenNumMacro"
# will divide the population of the town by the "SF" value to determine how many
# businesses of that type exist. Remainders are divided by the "SF" value to derive
# a percentage, which are the odds that one more of that business can be found.
# For instance, in a town of 5000 people, you'll find 2 artists, and possibly 3.
# 5000/2000 (the SF for artist) is 2.5. This means that you'll definitely have 2 artists
# (the "2" of 2.5), and a 50% chance (the ".5" of 2.5) of having a third. Another
# example: A town of 4350 people will have 5 blacksmiths, with a 44% chance of
# having a 6th (blacksmiths have an SF of 800, so 4350/800 = 5.44).
#
# Adjust the "SF" values to increase or decrease the number of business/services
# that will be generated in your town, villages, and such.

